Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the computation of the Cumulative Distribution Function (CDF) of the Signal-to-Interference-plus-Noise-Ratio (SINR) for a wireless link with a multi-antenna, Linear, Minimum-Mean-Square-Error (MMSE) receiver. This involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity, signal-to-noise ratio, etc. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless networks and the performance of multi-antenna MMSE receivers in non-homogenous Poisson networks. This involves networking and internet architecture concepts such as interference, network topology, etc. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the performance of wireless networks in the presence of interferers distributed according to a non-homogenous Poisson point process on the plane. This involves social and information network concepts such as network modeling, network analysis, etc. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the performance of multi-antenna MMSE receivers in wireless networks. This involves multiagent systems concepts such as distributed systems, coordination, etc.
